<p class="eyebrow">Wholesale rates</p>
<h1>Pricing</h1>
<p class="lede">Wholesale rates published in plain numbers. Origination, termination, messaging, DIDs, e911, port-in, and toll-free — all from <code>pricing.json</code>, no "contact sales" gates.</p>

<h2>What's not on this rate sheet</h2>
<p>STT, TTS, and recording storage are paid <strong>directly to your chosen provider</strong>. VoiceTel charges only its own line items — no per-character markup on Polly-style voices, no per-MB markup on S3 storage, no per-minute markup on transcription.</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Speech-to-text:</strong> Deepgram, Google, AWS, Azure, or any HTTP recogniser endpoint. Pay your provider's published rates.</li>
	<li><strong>Text-to-speech:</strong> any HTTP TTS endpoint (Piper, Coqui, OpenAI, ElevenLabs). Pay your provider directly.</li>
	<li><strong>Recording storage:</strong> bring your own S3 bucket. Pay AWS for storage you control. KMS encryption optional.</li>
</ul>

